<div class="wrap" style="padding-bottom:60px;">
  <div class="rules-grid">
    <div class="rule-item"><h2 class="rule-title">Paper Pattern</h2><div class="rule-body"><p><strong>Section A:</strong> 5 compulsory × 4 marks = 20</p><p><strong>Section B:</strong> 2 of 3 × 10 marks = 20</p><p><strong>Section C:</strong> 3 of 5 × 20 marks = 60</p><p>Total: 100 marks · 3-hour duration</p></div></div>
    <div class="rule-item"><h2 class="rule-title">Passing Marks</h2><div class="rule-body"><p><strong>36 out of 100</strong> (36%) per paper required.</p><p>Each paper must be cleared individually.</p></div></div>
    <div class="rule-item"><h2 class="rule-title">Back Paper Rules</h2><div class="rule-body"><p><strong>Fail 1-2 papers:</strong> Promoted. Clear as back papers.</p><p><strong>Fail 3+ papers:</strong> Semester back. Repeat entire semester.</p></div></div>
    <div class="rule-item"><h2 class="rule-title">Practical Papers</h2><div class="rule-body"><p><strong>K-3005</strong> (Sem III): Theory 50 + Project File 30 + Viva 20</p><p><strong>K-4007</strong> (Sem IV): Sessional Diary 40 + Field Work 40 + Viva 20</p><p><strong>K-5005</strong> (Sem V): Theory 50 + Exercises 40 + Viva 10</p><p><strong>K-6008</strong> (Sem VI): Moots 35 + Courts 25 + Interview 20 + Viva 10 + Diary 10</p></div></div>
    <div class="rule-item" style="grid-column:1/-1;"><h2 class="rule-title">Optional Subject Selection Guide</h2><div class="rule-body"><p style="color:var(--ink-60);margin-bottom:12px;font-size:13px;">Three semesters have optional papers. Choose ONE from each group.</p><p><strong style="color:var(--red);">Semester II:</strong> K-2005 Indian Legal History (essay-friendly) OR K-2006 Taxation (technical, most offered)</p><p><strong style="color:var(--red);">Semester IV:</strong> K-4004 Criminology (essay-friendly) OR K-4005 Trust Law (rare) OR K-4006 Banking Law (easiest, most offered)</p><p><strong style="color:var(--red);">Semester VI:</strong> K-6004 IP Law OR K-6005 Cyber Law OR K-6006 Women & Child OR K-6007 RTI (easiest)</p></div></div>
  </div>
</div>
